On Wednesday, August 17, 2005, at 09:51AM, George Lyle <glyle(-at-)pon.type2.com> wrote:

>I'm wondering about what damage graphite can do to a lock.  I've always
>understood that graphite was the lubricant of choice as it doesn't collect
>dust and lint.

I've not found it as effective and cleaning out the lock. Graphite just seems to gum it up.

FYI. After the lock is super clean and you put in a new key you'll also find that the edges on the key are so sharp it won't go in easily unless you lubricate the lock with triflow.

